JOHANNESBURG - The ANC is setting up camp for its policy conference at the Expo Centre in Soweto.It's a massive venue, with officials saying bigger is better. Hall 6 is the belly of the beast. This building will host nearly 5,000 people on the opening and closing days.Each delegate will get a seat at the table, but the party's top six will be more comfortable than most.When the speeches are over, the hard work begins.Delegates will break up into several conference rooms, each group discussing a different aspect of policy.It might sound intimate, but the average commission features more than 300 people.Hundreds of journalists will watch this all play out.Commissions will hold regular media briefings in a room in Hall 9.* Watch a full video report in the gallery above.eNCA